    "body":  "# The Civic Desk v0.3.2 public beta\n\nWindows-only public beta for CivicNewspaper / The Civic Desk.\n\n## Download\n\n- Installer: `The.Civic.Desk_0.3.2_x64-setup.exe`\n- SHA256: `1D6E650C44B44A74C5E7640097D2F8FF0618631D4C7311738229F424441F8BD5`\n- Size: `5250809` bytes\n- Checksum file: `SHA256SUMS.txt`\n\n## Current candidate\n\n- Product build commit: `ba49af4d69d2c4d6d88bfd148490494f243cc9d7`\n- Status: awaiting final cleanroom tester recheck for this rebuilt artifact.\n\nThis rebuild includes the prior v0.3.2 repairs plus durable draft persistence, linked-evidence Brief fallback, publish-preflight editor override, honest offline-AI drafting copy, generalized source-backed Brief classifiers, and release-body provenance checking.\n\n## Unsigned beta installer\n\nThis installer is unsigned because this is a free public beta. Windows SmartScreen may show a warning. Verify the SHA256 above against your download. If it matches, choose **More info**, then **Run anyway**.\n\n## Scope\n\n- Supported public-beta installer: Windows `.exe` only.\n- macOS and Linux installers are backlog/proof-needed and are not release-supported for v0.3.2.\n- Default live publishing proof path: anonymous here.now preview.\n- Credentialed external providers still need user-owned credentials and provider-specific proof.\n"
